# Water Dispenser Project

This project is designed to control and monitor a water dispenser using PlatformIO.

## Project Structure

The project structure is as follows:

```
waterdispenser/
├── include/            # Project-specific header files
├── lib/                # Libraries
├── src/                # Source files
│   ├── main.cpp        # Main application file
├── test/               # Unit tests
├── platformio.ini      # Project configuration file
```

## Features

- Dispense water with a button press
- Monitor water level
- Automatic refill when water level is low
- Display status on an LCD screen

## Requirements

- PlatformIO
- Arduino framework
- LCD display
- Water level sensor
- Relay module

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/waterdispenser.git
    ```
2. Open the project with PlatformIO IDE.
3. Build and upload the firmware to your microcontroller.

## Usage

1. Connect the hardware components as per the schematic.
2. Power on the system.
3. Use the button to dispense water and monitor the status on the LCD screen.

